# @base Package Authoring

## Workspace Context
This is the `SHARED/` pnpm workspace — home of all `@base/*` infrastructure packages.
- `@base/engine-core` — mount contract, EventBus, BaseModule (foundational — change carefully)
- `@base/ui` — Vue 3 component library
- `@base/pwa-core` — PWA service worker and offline utilities

Consumer projects (forks of `pwa-platform`) install these via GitHub Packages.

## Package Rules
- Every package is `"type": "module"` — no CommonJS
- Every package has `exports` field in package.json — no direct `dist/` path imports by consumers
- `peerDependencies` for Vue, not `dependencies` — consumers provide their own Vue
- Never add cross-dependencies between packages unless engine-core is the source — avoid circular deps

## Breaking Changes
- `@base/engine-core` interfaces (`EngineModule`, `ShellContext`, `EngineContext`) are the system contract
- Any change to these interfaces is a BREAKING CHANGE — bump major version and document migration
- All other packages: additive changes are minor, removals are major

## Publishing
- Target registry: GitHub Packages (`https://npm.pkg.github.com`)
- Scope: `@base`
- Run `pnpm build` in the package before `pnpm publish`
- Tag releases: `@base/engine-core@0.2.0`, not just `v0.2.0`

## Testing a Package Locally Before Publishing
Use `pnpm link` from within the package, then `pnpm link @base/<name>` in the consumer project.
